# NestJS — architecture overview (slice layout)

## Desired state

This document applies when the **shell** is **NestJS**: injectable use cases, modules, and controllers. It complements the language-agnostic **vertical slice** and **hexagonal** rules under `rules/00-architecture/`.

**Cursor** loads more specific rule files for each layer; prefer opening the file that matches the code you edit.

## Stack (illustrative)

| Layer        | Technology |
|-------------|------------|
| Language    | TypeScript (strict) |
| Shell       | NestJS (`@Injectable` use cases, controllers, modules) |
| Core        | `fp-ts` and/or `Effect` — errors as values in domain where adopted |
| Validation  | Zod or `@effect/schema` at HTTP and persistence edges |

## Canonical layout

```text
src/
  modules/
    <feature>/
      domain/                    # Pure functions — rules R1–R4
        <feature>.model.ts
        <feature>.logic.ts
      application/
        use-cases/               # Rule 5 — orchestration
      infrastructure/
        persistence/            # Rule 6 — e.g. sql_* repositories
        http/                     # Rule 6 — controllers, DTOs, gateways
  shared/
    domain/                      # Cross-cutting types — rule 7
    infrastructure/              # Shared clients
```

